, 244. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1988,2014]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body vermiform; scapular tubercles and setae on rear shield margin, scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[1402,1426,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">sc</emphasis>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,158,309]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
directed posteriorly; anterolateral setae on coxisternum I (
<emphasis box="[852,881,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">1b</emphasis>
) absent; tibial seta present, empodium entire; opisthosoma dorsoventral annuli subequal, with granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,158,309]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
This genus consists of 7 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,242,268]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,242,267]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
